        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 23 at 2:38PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 238 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Tuckers Crossroad, or
near Wrightsville. This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Lovett, Spann, Tuckers Crossroad, Donovan, and Wrightsville.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
